Title: Home prices down 18% in 2008
Description: Home prices are back to their March 2004 levels, having dropped in 20 major U.S. cities by 2.2% in October and by a record 18% from the previous year,

Title: U.S. bankruptcy filings up 31% in 2008
Description: The U.S. House of Representatives is expected to approve a bill that would let judges erase mortgage debt for homeowners who enter bankruptcy as a last resort.

Title: Bankrupty Filings Continue Decline
Description: Bankruptcy filings for the 12-month period ending June 30, 2012, totaled 14 percent less than in the 12-month period ending June 30, 2011

Title: Foreclosures on the Rise
Description: Nevada tops the list with 7.3% foreclosure rate, followed by Arizona and Florida (4.5%) and California (4%)
